reviews.text:
It's one of those Asian bakeries that cater towards the taste for sweet soft bread. The sourdough is a complete joke, it almost tastes like supermarket bread and is expensive for it's size. 
The baguette is so so, the pastries may be better but I haven't tried any.
Really good... a must @ popcorn
A good stop for you buying coffee before movies. Convenient pick up point.
I like it here, but don’t know how much longer could I afford afternoon delight in here.
Very nice bakery. You can get coffee and bread for HKD 26 to 36.
